7:
Sir... Something about this place
doesn't seem right.
9:
I know, I know... It's not a place to
bring a rookie, but we had no other
choice.
11:
Don't you remember the briefing?
AltMeme has launched an attack on
DAN and they've asked for backup.
13:
But do we really need all of 3MM out
here? Sounds like a full-blown war...
15:
It could get ugly... DAN isn't a
company you want to mess around
with...
18:
Welp. We get hazard pay for this,
right?
20:
Yeah... As long as we don't come
back in body bags, that is.
27:
*gulp* What sort of firepower is
AltMeme packing?!
31:
I can't even see the bottom... Sir,
what should we do?
34:
Get back, rookie! Remember your
training! We need to cordon—
36:
...How much training did you say she
had?
37:
She's still a newbie. Maybe we
shouldn't have brought her to such
a high-stakes operation...
42: Ouch... That was one hell of a fall...
47: I-I need to get back to them...
53:
This is bad, I can barely move... Even
my prosthetics are not responding...
Is this where it all ends?
57:
I graduate from a no-name school,
join a security company, only to just
die like this?
59:
What a joke... I can just about
laugh... If only it didn't hurt so much...
64:
*sigh* I wonder how hard mom will
take the news? Dad will probably
survive... But still...
69:
I hope that workers' compensation
pays out...
75:
Wh-what?! Please, dock my pay if
you have to, but don't fire me!
86:
Welcome to Starview Village. My
name is Stella.
95:
Ahaha... That bump must have
knocked you out good. I'm Alk, nice
to meet you!
99:
Hi? My name is Katyusha. I work for a
security company called 3MM...
104:
Can you tell me where I am? This
isn't one of AltMeme's resorts, is it?
Oh no... Would my insurance even
cover this?!
107:
The first thing you think about after
getting hurt is your insurance? It
must be hard living in Qualia City...
110:
But there's no need to worry about
that. How about some food?
115:
Is that all-natural?! There's no way I
could afford that...
118:
Don't worry, you're in Starview
Village. Not Qualia City.
123:
Unfortunately, we don't have any
AdTaste, so I hope this will do!
There's more where that comes
from, so eat up!
133:
So you're saying this is... another
world? That sounds like a sci-fi story
you'd read online...
135: Alk... Stella... Could I ask a favor?
144:
Okay. I already welcomed you,
though.
149:
Even if I went back, I'll probably get
suspended... or worse—fired! And
don't even get me started on having
to eat plain SoyMate with no ads...
151:
I feel like I'll never get a chance like
this ever again. I'll do anything...
Please...
160:
What do you mean? There must be
something you want in return...
163:
Certainly, we will need your help in
the near future.
172:
Anyways! That sounds like a good
place to leave off for today, so eat
up and get some rest!
178:
...I hope I didn't just join a cult or
something.
